-- Factbox: SandRidge payments to CEO and his family
-- 
-- Mon Jan 14, 2013 1:31pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/14/us-sandridge-factbox-idUSBRE90D0X820130114

 

 (Reuters) - 
 SIDE DEALS SandRidge Energy has paid millions of dollars to chief executive Tom Ward and his family, in addition to his salary and bonus, including: * $5 million to lease property and pay royalties to WCT Resources, a Ward family-controlled energy company * Nearly $4 million in royalties to TLW Land & Cattle, an Oklahoma firm controlled by Ward * More than $18 million to sponsor and license the Oklahoma City Thunder basketball team, in which Ward owns a 19 percent interest * Nearly $850,000 to buy tickets to "various sporting and other entertainment events" from Ward Source: SEC filings (Reporting By  Michael Erman ; Editing by Patricia Kranz)